<figureCitation box="[1085,1162,1332,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1928,1950]" captionTargetBox="[184,1418,265,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-50@4.[151,1436,245,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogenetic tree generated from Bayesian Inference (BI) based on the combined dataset of ITS-rDNA, GAPDH, RPB2, TEF1-α and Alt a 1 for 44 Alternaria strains. The Bayesian posterior probabilities (&gt;0.75) and RAxML Maximum likelihood and Maximum parsimony bootstrap values (&gt;50%) are given at the nodes (PP/ML/MP). The tree was rooted to A. gypsophilae CBS 107.41 and A. vaccariae CBS 116533 (Alternaria sect. Gypsophilae) and the newly identified strains are in bold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5508903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5508903/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="187">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1176,1191,1332,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1947,1969]" captionTargetBox="[167,1426,215,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-23@5.[151,1436,190,1923]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Alternaria guilanica (IRAN 4220C). a. Colony on V8-A after 7 days. b–c. sporulation pattern on V8-A. d–f. Conidiophores. g–x. conidia. Bars = 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5508905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5508905/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="187">2</figureCitation>
